Syucopation in modern music, my colleague, Professor Spalding, informs me, always gives an enlivening effect; whatever the sentiment may be that is conveyed by the verses to which the music is set, and it may greatly vary, inversion oi stress animates the melody. It is precisely the device, therefore, that we should expect to find applied in ‘logaoedic’ verse, which, to characterize it briefly, is a vigorous metre of all work.
